$ cmd.exe - color
@ color

`color` sets → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe[cmd.exe's] console's foreground and background → design/graphic/color[color] using two (hexadecimal) digits in the range from `0` … `f`.

The first digit specifies the background color, the second one the foreground color: the range 8…F repeats the color of the range 0…7, yet lighter or brighter:
table { ll
  0 / 8 ☰ black / grey 
  1 / 9 ☰ blue 
  2 / A ☰ green
  3 / B ☰ aqua
  4 / C ☰ red
  5 / D ☰ purple
  6 / E ☰ yellow
  7 / F ☰ white 
table }

Thus, the following command sets the background to the dark version of blue and the foreground to the light version of yellow:
code {
color 1e
code }

`color` without arguments resets the colors to its defaults.

`color` is affected by whether → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/command-extension[command extensions] are enabled or disabled.

sa:
  → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands
